                "sections": [
                    {
                        "title": "Common Ground",
                        "content": "<p>Psychedelics and cyberdelics share remarkable common ground. Before we explore their differences, it's essential to understand what they have in common. This isn't about competition between two opposing approaches—it's about recognizing two paths toward similar destinations.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Shared Intention"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Shared Intention",
                        "content": "<p>Both psychedelics and cyberdelics exist for the same fundamental purpose: facilitating consciousness exploration, personal transformation, and spiritual development. Whether using substances or technology, the underlying intention is identical—to expand awareness, facilitate healing, and support personal growth.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Shared Outcomes"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Shared Outcomes",
                        "media": {
                            "type": "image",
                            "src": "../assets/images/module1/lesson2/parallel_paths.jpg",
                            "alt": "Parallel paths merging toward a shared destination"
                        },
                        "mediaLayout": "full",
                        "content": "<p>Research shows that both approaches can produce similar outcomes. Mystical experiences, therapeutic breakthroughs, perspective shifts, emotional healing, and spiritual insights can occur through either path. The phenomenology—what people actually experience—can be remarkably similar.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Research Validation"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Research Validation",
                        "content": "<p>Studies comparing traditional psychedelic experiences with properly designed cyberdelic experiences show comparable scores on measures of mystical experience, ego dissolution, and therapeutic benefit. This isn't speculation—it's empirically validated. Both approaches can facilitate profound shifts in consciousness when done intentionally and skillfully.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Test Understanding"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
